1. ESSENTIAL VOCABULARY - QUICK REFERENCE
================================================================================

CORE CONCEPTS:
• MLOps = Machine Learning + Operations (putting ML models into production)
• LSTM = Long Short-Term Memory (neural network that reads text sequentially)
• Microservices = Small independent programs working together
• Docker = Container system (each service in its own isolated box)
• API = How services talk to each other over HTTP

ML TERMS:
• Classification = Sorting into categories (27 product categories)
• Preprocessing = Cleaning text before model reads it
• Tokenization = Words → Numbers (model only reads numbers)
• Padding = Making all sequences exactly 10 numbers long
• Embedding = Turn numbers into 128-dimensional vectors
• Epoch = One full pass through training data (we use 10)
• Batch Size = How many examples per update (we use 32)
• Softmax = Final layer, gives probabilities for 27 categories

INFRASTRUCTURE:
• API Gateway = Front door, checks tokens, routes requests (port 8080)
• Flask = Python web framework for all our services
• Token = Random key proving who you are (64 hex characters)
• Authentication = WHO you are (username + password)
• Authorization = WHAT you can do (admin vs user roles)
• SHA-256 = Password hashing (one-way scrambling)

MONITORING & TOOLS:
• Prometheus = Collects metrics every 15 seconds (port 9090)
• Grafana = Makes charts from Prometheus data (port 3000)
• PromQL = Query language for Prometheus
• MLflow = Experiment tracking, saves all training runs (port 5000)
• Airflow = Task orchestration, runs workflows (port 8081)
• DAG = Directed Acyclic Graph (chain of tasks in order)
• DVC = Data Version Control (like Git but for big files)
• CI/CD = Automated testing on every code push


