2. PROJECT OVERVIEW - KEYPOINTS
================================================================================

WHAT IT DOES:
• Input: Product description text (e.g., "Samsung Galaxy smartphone...")
• Output: Category + Confidence (e.g., "Electronics, 85%")
• 27 possible categories
• Uses LSTM neural network for classification

THE 13 DOCKER CONTAINERS:
1. Web UI (8082) - Dashboard website, served by Nginx
2. API Gateway (8080) - Front door, checks tokens, routes requests
3. Auth Service (5004) - Login, passwords, tokens
4. Data Service (5001) - Load CSV, clean data, split train/val/test
5. Training Service (5002) - Train LSTM, log to MLflow
6. Prediction Service (5003) - Load model, make predictions
7. MLflow (5000) - Experiment tracking, model registry
8. Airflow Webserver (8081) - Workflow UI
9. Airflow Scheduler - Runs DAG tasks automatically
10. Airflow DB (PostgreSQL) - Stores Airflow metadata
11. Airflow Init - One-time setup (then exits)
12. Prometheus (9090) - Metrics collection
13. Grafana (3000) - Visualization dashboards

PREDICTION FLOW (10 STEPS):
1. User types text in browser → clicks "Classify"
2. Browser sends text + token → API Gateway (8080)
3. Gateway → Auth Service: "Is token valid?"
4. Auth Service → Gateway: "Yes, user=admin, role=admin"
5. Gateway → Prediction Service: forwards text
6. Prediction Service: cleans text (remove HTML, stopwords, lemmatize)
7. Prediction Service: tokenize → pad to length 10
8. LSTM model predicts → returns 27 probabilities
9. Highest probability = answer (map number → category name)
10. Result → Gateway → Browser → User sees category + confidence

RETRAINING FLOW (4 AIRFLOW TASKS):
1. Task 1: Data Service cleans new data
2. Task 2: Training Service starts training (background thread)
3. Task 3: Poll every 10s: "Training done?" (wait max 1 hour)
4. Task 4: Prediction Service reloads new model from disk

THE 5 ARCHITECTURE DIAGRAMS:
1. Complete Architecture - All 13 containers, 6 layers
2. Microservices Communication - How services talk (arrows)
3. ML Pipeline - 7 steps from data → prediction
4. Monitoring Architecture - Prometheus → Grafana flow
5. Technology Stack - 5 layers of tools from infrastructure → UI


